---
import InternWiki from '../../layouts/InternWiki.astro';

export const title = "Networking Coffee";
export const description = "Strategic execution of informational interviews during your internship.";
export const category = "Professional Development";
export const order = 10;
---

<InternWiki title={title} description={description} category={category} order={order}>
	<h2>The Outreach Strategy</h2>
	<p>Informational coffees are the primary mechanism for converting a summer internship into a full-time return offer. Do not limit outreach to your immediate team. Target alumni from your university working in adjacent departments.</p>
	
	<h3>The Cold Email</h3>
	<p>Keep initial outreach below five sentences. State your name, your current intern role, your shared connection (e.g., alumni status), and a direct request for a 15-minute coffee chat. Propose two specific time windows. Never ask an executive to accommodate your schedule.</p>

	<h2>Meeting Execution</h2>
	<p>The intern is responsible for managing the logistics of the meeting.</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Payment:</strong> Always offer to pay for the senior employee's coffee. They will almost certainly decline and pay for yours using a corporate card, but the offer demonstrates professional etiquette.</li>
		<li><strong>Location:</strong> Suggest a coffee shop located directly in or adjacent to their office building. Minimize their transit time.</li>
		<li><strong>Question Framework:</strong> Do not ask questions that can be answered via the company intranet. Ask about their specific career trajectory, team structural challenges, and their macro outlook on the industry.</li>
		<li><strong>Time Discipline:</strong> Conclude the conversation at exactly the 15-minute mark. Say, "I want to be respectful of your time, so I will let you get back to your day." If they wish to continue speaking, they will signal it.</li>
	</ul>
</InternWiki>
